pullRequest.body:
We add custom delaborators for the following notations, introduced in #20688:

- `[m]‚Çô`, which denotes the `m`-dimensional simplex in the `n`-truncated simplex category. If `pp.proofs` is set to `true`, we also pretty-print the proof `p : m ‚â§ n` as `[m,p]‚Çô`.
- `X _[m]‚Çô`, which denotes the `m`-th term of an `n`-truncated (co)simplicial object `X`. If `pp.proofs` is set to `true`, we also pretty-print the proof `p : m ‚â§ n` as `X _[m,p]‚Çô`.

---

This PR/issue depends on:
* leanprover-community/mathlib4#20688
By **[Dependent Issues](https://github.com/z0al/dependent-issues)** (ü§ñ). Happy coding!
<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->

The following test, taken from [`#17732`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17732/files#diff-40ab7cd5656f9da110091d345b5b90bc73d7183951a1a663c173a51a585acca2R24-R31), shows that our delaborator attempts to pretty-print some terms even when the truncation level cannot be subscripted. 

I'm not aware of a fix for this that would still allow pretty-printing things like `[m]‚Çô‚Çä‚ÇÅ`, but any suggestions would be appreciated. It also might not matter, as I can't think of any cases where the difference between  `[m]‚Çô` and `[m]n‚úù` would be all that confusing.

```lean
import Mathlib.AlgebraicTopology.SimplexCategory
open SimplexCategory.Truncated

variable (n : ‚Ñï) (m : ‚Ñï) (h : m ‚â§ n) (x) (hx : x = [m]‚Çô) (n : True)

/- The delaborator should ideally not fire here because the truncation level is now `n‚úù`,
which cannot be subscripted. -/
/-- info: hx : x = [m]n‚úù -/
#guard_msgs in #check hx
```

Edit: Fixed in commits [5d41e60](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20719/commits/5d41e60645ca700057a63336ef77d406ae438b77) and [f4d15c3](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20719/commits/f4d15c31717976734ae09c6685d3b598659eb0bf).

pullRequest.title: feat(AlgebraicTopology): delaborators for truncated simplicial notations
